ZH: 我无法驱使自己去跑步。
EN: I can't motivate myself to go for a run.

ZH: 她的成功驱使着我向前努力。
EN: Her success drives me to strive harder.

ZH: 老师用自己的故事来驱使学生们努力学习。
EN: The teacher uses their own stories to compel the students to study hard.

ZH: 他受到竞争对手的压力驱使，变得更有动力了。
EN: He became more motivated under the pressure from his competitors.

ZH: 这个新发现将会驱使科学界进一步研究。
EN: This new discovery will drive further research in the scientific community.

ZH: 他的指导驱使我改变了对这个问题的看法。
EN: His guidance compelled me to change my view on this issue.

ZH: 这个故事驱使我们思考人类存在的意义。
EN: This story prompts us to contemplate the meaning of human existence.

ZH: 需要更多的刺激来驱使我们进一步努力。
EN: We need more incentives to motivate us to strive even harder.

